 The general formula for the slope is going to be
\begin_inset Formula \[
m=\frac{\ln 2-\ln x}{2-x}.\]

\end_inset 

Note that while the question in Steward require 6 decimal places values
 for the slope, we give only 3 decimal places below.
\begin_deeper 
\layout Enumerate

For 
\begin_inset Formula \( x=1.5 \)
\end_inset 

, we have
\begin_inset Formula \[
m=\frac{\ln 2-\ln 1.5}{2-1.5}\cong 0.575.\]

\end_inset 


\layout Enumerate

